beer.beer_description:
Deep orange in colour, this ESB delivers sweet malt aromas of toffee and raspberry, under pinned by an earthy hop bouquet.
On the palate, the initially sweet marmalade and fruit bun flavours give way to nuttiness and a restrained bitterness.
Using Nitrogen rather than CO2 with the beer produces a smoother, thicker mouth feel and less perceived bitterness as Nitrogen is mostly insoluble.
